Review: another addition to the i wish I had this on vhs as a kid cannon, sublime :)

hmmm what to SAY. This christmas was kinda a shitshow… (mom’s 2nd husband may be a narcissist but tbd).. However this movie exists, and is perfect, and I cried though the whole thing even the scenes that aren’t “sad” because the whole thing is just too perfect it hurts. Every time I watch this I get so much more out of it and different characters feel more relatable. Some thoughts on this christmas, full family, watch of this masterpiece:-Jo…

This movie fills me with rage.  There are few characters I like less than Mackenzie Davis’s character in this. The fact that they end up together is…… a choice. yiiikes. fuuuuck. I remeber feeling this way the first time I watched it but it was somehow worse on this watch, god. Doesn’t help that Kristen is acting everyone off the fucking screen, and the only one who rises to her level is Aubrey Plaza (and Alison Brie in moments). The…

I finally feel myself coming around to Hugh Grant… hmmmm. I however hate Martin Freeman and this did nothing to change that. Still confused how the Kiera Knightly and the guy from the walking dead’s story ended up, was the implication at the end that they were a throuple with her husband? Odd. January Jones is that you ?????

OMG THIS RULES, some scattered thoughts:-Suuuuuch good Pacino- Did Micheal Mann invent shooting office movies like action movies?? -McGill’s big court scene?????????? UMMM, YES -*added to my intimate epics list*-the nighttime scenes of course, still confused why Mann’s nighttime scenes make everyone else’s look like garbage.-The women and wives specifically are so poorly written, Christopher Nolan would be proud.-why can’t Pacino answer his own phone or make is own calls?
Albert Finny saying, “like all great ladies, she still has her secret ways” to Judy Dench with a sluty twinkle in his eye.. I gasped, I giggled, I would also shoot my shot with Judy.

From the marketing and trailer I was worried this might not be my speed, and did have some issues: dragged in the middle bit, Jerod Carmichael is like inexplicably terrible and every single one of of his scenes was painful to get through, visually some of the long shots didn’t work for me and the occasional set looked off as well mostly cause they were in contrast to such beautiful and compelling ones. BUT THAT SAID, I found this very…
wtf how have I never seen this, it fucking RULES. Best Emma Stone ????
Many things, but def good reminder of how brutal living on the east coast can be. Sad christmas movies >>
Dysfunctional family drama set at Christmas may be the best movie genre.
